title: 9_11 911 Pentagon Attack - Behind the Smoke Curtain - Barbara Ho
description:
Barbara Honegger, "Behind the Smoke Curtain", January 2013

Evidence that an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) exploded on the ground outside the Pentagon wall near the fire house next to the helipad on the morning of September 11, 2001. Two firemen on duty saw the plane approach and were burned when it exploded. They survived. The explosion happened about five minutes before the official report.

Also evidence that bombs exploded inside the pentagon a few minutes before the plane exploded outside the pentagon.
